The paper proposes a static analysis method for concurrent programs, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The method uses a system of constraints to model the causality ordering of interferences, which relates to logic in computer science (cs.LO) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper mentions scalability and termination guarantees, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
